name: Coles Melbourne CBD
review_text:
As I stood in line at the self-service checkouts, I couldn't help but notice the commotion happening at the adjacent register. Manisha, the employee, was visibly upset and yelling at a customer who had asked for her assistance. The customer appeared just as shocked and taken aback as I was.

I couldn't believe how unprofessional Manisha was being. It's one thing to have a bad day, but it's another to take it out on customers who are simply asking for help. As I approached the self service, I hesitated to even make eye contact with Manisha, fearing I too would be met with a similar reaction.

Sure enough, as the next customer approached the self service, Manisha raised her voice once again. It was clear that her behaviour was not an isolated incident, but rather a pattern of poor customer service. I couldn't help but feel frustrated and disappointed in the way I was being treated.

name: Coles Melbourne CBD
review_text: The quintescence of melbourne lifestyle. More than a grocery store, Coles Melbourne CBD is before anything else a community safehaven, a place for Melbournians to congregate and exchange ideas, a place for freindships to form and for families to reunite. A place for hungry and satiated to find happiness alike, for tourist and locals to  discover or rediscover what makes Melbourne magical. Coles Melbourne CBD is thus also a place of reunion and celebration, ideal for wedding, bar mitzvahs, baptisms and funerals alike. I would take my grandma there if I could. I can now die peacefully knowing that I have been able to give meaning to my previously meaningless life the second i laid my eyes on the crimson doorstep of Coles Melbourne CBD. I will never be the same person as I was before, a true elevated being, blessed by the presence of such an institution in the city whose sidewalks I tread everyday.

Went there earlier this week and seemed to be the same:

review_text: I bought a bag of chips a few days ago and I had it in my bag. I took it with me to hang out with my friends and we ended up not eating it. Upon leaving the store, a security guard with dark skin stopped me and checked my bag and saw the bag of chips, and then demanded me to show the receipt. I explained to him that I did not have it because I rarely print receipts and that was a few days ago. He continued on to ask me to prove that I bought it. He said I was supposed to bring the receipt with me even though it was bought a few days ago. He said he had to suspect that I stole it. I told him if he didn‚Äôt believe me he could check the camera. I did not put anything into my bag when I was in the shop. I didn‚Äôt even go to the snack aisle. He could not prove it so he let me go but I left feeling embarrassed and distressed. A very traumatizing shopping experience.

name: Coles Melbourne Central
review_text:
Mei 2023

Supermarket menjual berbagai macam kebutuhan sehari-hari. Dari roti, makanan siap saji, minuman, snack, coklat, permen, bumbu masak, mie instant, sabun, sampo, daging, makanan beku, perabotan, gift card, dan lain sebagainya. Banyak produk-produk yang diskon atau bundle (beli 2 harga lebih murah). Lokasinya lumayan banyak tersebar di mall-mall dan tempat publik seperti stasiun kereta.

Pembayaran bisa menggunakan cash, kartu debit, kartu kredit, applepay dan googlepay. Ada kassa mandiri, bisa scan dan bayar langsung. Kalau takut salah bisa antri di kassa manual yang dijaga oleh pegawai.

Bawa tas belanja sendiri karena tidak disediakan kantong plastik. Kalau mau pakai kantong harus beli. Ada yang dari plastik, kertas coklat (paper bag), dan kain.

Three reasons for the poor rating.
1. Young guy at the self serve checkout tonight told my wife and I that there is to be only one person using the checkout at a time (social distancing), I say fair enough and walk outside to wait.
Next minute 3 young girls enter the self serve area, the guy cleans a checkout down and proceeds to gesture to them to use the register, all 3 of them together use it and not a peep from the guy. This is discriminatory behavior.
2. I ordered over $100 worth of groceries online to pick up at this store, waited for an excessive line of commission flats residents to buy cigarettes (online pick up and cigarette purchase are at a shared counter). Fair enough, I wait my turn. When I get to the front of the queue, I show the attendant my order, he ASKS ME TO WAIT while he serves another dero buying cigarettes behind me in the line. Then the dero can‚Äôt decide which cigarettes he wants, so we all stand there while he ums and errs.
3. I was walking out one day when a dero made off with some groceries that he hadn‚Äôt paid for, staff started chasing him and in the process one of the larger female staff waddled behind them and knocked me into the sliding doors while I was exiting. (Great way to treat paying customers) She was useless in the pursuit anyway, too slow.

Besides the poor service, this store is small, cramped, has limited items available, and always has a plethora of foul mouthed, foul smelling, aggressive beggars at the entrance all the time.
I‚Äôve given them 3 chances, they‚Äôll never have my business again.

The store was clean and well-organized, and the staff were friendly and helpful. I had no issues finding the coconut water or checking out. Overall, I had a great experience at Coles and will definitely be returning in the future.

I highly recommend stopping by Coles if you're in need of coconut water or any other groceries. You never know what amazing deals you might find!

Happy shopping!

name: Coles Port Melbourne
review_text:
There a few things in life that you can't avoid, death, taxes and giong to the supermarket for your weekly shop. Usually when I used to think of the weekly shop I tried to avoid it, but now since I discovered Coles port melbourne i have looked forward to coming to coles port melbourne for my weekly shop. We have lived in Japan for a few years and the supermarket scene is very very good there, often when im walking through the aisles of coles port melbourne i feel nostalgic of my weekly shopping experience in tokyo. Why is this? Well firstly as i enter the rear exit down the elevator, I am delighted so see fresh flowers at the entry; as well as a very big and well planned vegetable/fruit section. The layout of this coles is spacious and there is always plenty of stock available at almost any time. Usually as couples do, my wife and I sometimes have small arguments about what we want to cook for dinner, but as soon as we go to the vegetable section we find inspiration. On another note, the music playlist is pretty good for a supermarket.

Keep up the great work, you should be proud.

review_text:
Every time I visit this supermarket the Indian guy managing the checkouts either calls security to stand right behind me and watch me scan, or he stands right behind me himself.

He did so again tonight, and after I paid and received my long receipt, and I turned around to leave, he looked me in the eyes and then lifted a microphone that was hanging around his neck (the type that comes with earphones/earbuds) and said, "All good, all good."

I have never stolen anything in my life. I work at a high paying job, and my purchases at Coles are always relatively high (usually > $100), i.e., I am a non-stealing good customer. He must've seen me come in a thousand times already and I've never stolen a thing.

So I cannot understand why I must always go through this kind of obvious harassment. I can only think that it must be some kind of discriminatory/racial profiling that he is choosing to implement.

review_text: Parking is good and bad, free for 90 minutes when you spend $30 at Coles which is great but the parking machine never works properly, despite it being upgraded, the only one in the city that fails to consistently work. Coles offer coinless (free) trolleys which is great. Not a big store but has almost all types of items but limited by variety in each category. Gets quite busy with narrow Isles. The area in which it's located has shady characters, sometimes in the parking area, but it is the city and it is a central commute hub, nothing of concern even at early hours of the morning. Staff are quite good, had an issue one time, sent in a complaint in writing, that one time, the only time I've ever complained because the staff member was super rude, but management dealt with it professionally with a bunch of options, timely, and took the matter seriously with great assurances. It's the preferred Coles in the city area for me and would be better if Wilson fixed their damn parking machine, no fault of Coles but as an extension, it reduces the experience.

name: Coles Collingwood
review_text: April 1914 first Coles store opens on Smith Street, Collingwood. Today the original Coles store looks as good as the day it opened. I remember when people would mostly visit Smith Street to shop, visit post office and buy a lotto ticket. If I had to say anything negative,  it would be that during Covid, I've been disappointed with how slow this Coles was in getting themselves 'Covid Safe'. Whilst other supermarkets moved quickly, getting the 'spit screens', doing regular cleaning of trolleys and baskets, this Coles was the last to do so. And unfortunately, about 3 out of the last 5 visits, I've noticed the baskets have been dirty, suggesting theyre not always getting wiped cleaned before being put back near the entry, ready for use.
But I'm still giving them 5 stars because the staff are working so hard during this time and the delay in the screens etc was not their fault!  So keep up the good work guys, your a great little store and you guys do the Coles name proud!!

review_text: Such a huge improvement over the old Coles! It's the same size but feels so much bigger with the new layout. Quality of produce is improved and there are lots of nice touches and new products including more of a focus on vegetarian and gluten free foods. Plus there's a wider range of ready-to-eat meals, which will be a bonus for tourists and backpackers. Also, it feels like there are more staff working there, more tills are open, and the new and improved staff are a lot friendlier (maybe they're happy being in the new store). And best of all, there are no more ridiculously high shelves that people my height can't reach!

review_text:
Friday 6 June 2022 Time around 3:30 pm
Why?  REFUSAL TO HONOR PRICE  THAT WAS GIVEN BY A STAFF MEMBER AFTER CHECKING IT.

Facts
Golden Circle 2 L Long Life Juice Varieties were on special $3.50.  I asked a staff member to check the price of the Golden Circle Pineapple.  They went out the back and returned with a scanner.  They scanned the Pineapple Juice  and then scanned a Ticket. They  checked their work by scanning the ticket again and rescanned the Pineapple Juice to check the price.   They then stated The Pineapple Juice was $3.50.

"Thank you. I asked you to check as sometimes there are exceptions to Specials."The staff member replied. "All the Golden Circle 2 L Long Life Juice Varieties are on special.  They are $3.50."

The Pineapple Juice scanned at $4.80 - a difference of $1.30.  I asked for a price check specifying which staff member I spoke to to for them to check the price again.

The Service Register Manager (claimed she she was the Acting Store Manager REFUSED to believe the Staff Member and told me that The Staff member had Misspoken.  That is a COLES problem.

I said Goodbye and left and they further REFUSED to calll the staff member to check what they said.

The Store manager was not available to discuss this.

And that is why Coles St Kilda gets a 1 STAR Rating for IGNORING what the Coles Staff said what the price was .

name: Coles St Kilda
review_text: Hmmm. The lovely staff are still here at the new gorgeous look Coles, but there are some negatives. Gone is the deli which means buying prawns to sliced meats is now a pre packaged (and in more plastic) moment. Fish options have shrunk and the price for fresh salmon has increased (because you can‚Äôt buy it by the piece... because there‚Äôs no deli). And the initial glamorous additions aren‚Äôt traveling as well a few weeks in: the pineapple peeler is ok but not when all the ready to be peeled pineapples are green; the noisette branded almond croissants and Portuguese tarts are soggy; the range of daggy packet sweet biscuits has been decimated in favour of the gourmet offerings in the glamour party food section. Maybe this version of the new Coles is a seasonal party version too and when school goes back, a bit of core food options may again take up floor space. It‚Äôs nice to embrace change but the team would do well to monitor things carefully. It‚Äôs a blunt statement but our share household of formerly local Coles shoppers has tested the new Coles, enjoyed the buzz but have gone back to tired old (but hugely functional) Woolworths.

name: Coles Burwood East
review_text:
I used to like shopping here until they changed all of the registers to self serve - I really dislike going through an entire store and not being acknowledged by a single person.

There have been plenty of times when I've gotten to the register and needed help and no one was there, I've looked over at an 'attendant' and they've ignored me or I've been directed to a checkout where someone will help and then there's just no one there. One time I even walked up with my trolley and the guy working asked if I'd like some help to which I said yes, and he just ignored my response and walked away. He then reappeared 5 minutes or so later while I was still scanning and I showed him a pizza box I had that had opened so asked for another one, he scanned the item and told me to just go back through the store when I was done to get another one. So unhelpful!

Yesterday there was only 2 sets of the 2 self serve registers open and everyone there was elderly apart from myself. You can see people are confused and not really sure what's going on. There definitely should have been more registers open because all of them had queues and not enough space for all of the trolleys, an elderly lady even bumped me with her trolley.

Shopping here is becoming seriously annoying. I'm only giving my review two stars because there is one girl that works here with purple hair who is always helpful and she deserves to be acknowledged.

I only shop here because it's the supermarket closest to my house however I am seriously considering trying out other shops because of how much I dislike going here now.

I don't shop at Aldi mainly due to the staff not helping customers packing their shopping but this Coles outlet is even worse. name: Coles Burwood East
review_text:
Coles Super Market in Burwood East, Vic. area is a very popular shopping centre for your daily needs.  A huge and attractive variety of garment, shoes, bakery  confectionary, poultry and dairy products, vegetables etc. are available at reasonable prices.  Grocery center has a very good variety for different section of society including chines, asians etc.  Most of the reputed Indian Food brands i.e. Haldiram, Parle, MDH spices, Pachranga pickles and much more is avalable.

Location is very convenient, lot of parking, courteous staff, very systematic, neat n clean.  You can definitely visit this place for your routine and even occasional shopping.
